    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER AUTOMATE-2 - REMOVE - MAINSHAFT AND COUNTERSHAFTS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="7">
        <title>MAINSHAFT AND COUNTERSHAFTS</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Attach the gear shaft lifting fixture (ZTSE 4288) to the countershafts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302255">Figure 55</hotlnk>). Secure it with bolts from the countershaft reverse gears.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302255" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302255" filename="../figg13/G1302255.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 55. Attach Gear Shift Lifting Fixture</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the assembly from the clutch housing by lifting it and sliding it out of overdrive
                fork (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302256">Figure 56</hotlnk>). Remove all fork assemblies from the mainshaft assembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302256" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302256" filename="../figg13/G1302256.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 56. Lift Assembly From Clutch Housing</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>When moving heavy parts, use a chain hoist to help prevent personal injury.</para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Overdrive fork can stay in the case unless it needs to be replaced (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302257">Figure 57</hotlnk>). If the overdrive shift fork shoes are worn, replace them.
                It is not necessary to remove the fork to replace the fork shoes.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302257" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302257" filename="../figg13/G1302257.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 57. Overdrive Fork</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To remove the overdrive shift fork, first remove the snap ring (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302258">Figure 58</hotlnk>). Push the pin through the bracket. Lift the fork from the
                unit.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302258" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302258" filename="../figg13/G1302258.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 58. Remove Snap Ring</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The 5th speed gear is removed next (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302259">Figure 59</hotlnk>). Remove and replace the bearing cups if they are damaged.
                The oil troughs can remain with the case.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302259" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302259" filename="../figg13/G1302259.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 59. 5th Speed Gear Removal</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If the unit is equipped with a neutral safety start switch, it can be removed and inspected
                now (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302260">Figure 60</hotlnk>). Replace it if it is worn or damaged.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302260" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302260" filename="../figg13/G1302260.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 60. Neutral Safety Start Switch</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Set the shafts in the assembly stand (ZTSE4286) (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302261">Figure 61</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302261" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302261" filename="../figg13/G1302261.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 61. Shafts In Assembly Stand</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
